<article id="node-15841">
<h1 >6.7.3.90 Waiver of Debts of a Particular Class</h1>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>SSAct section 1237AB enables the Secretary to waive debts arising under or as a result of the SSAct, if they are included in a class of debts which has been specified by the Minister by legislative instrument.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 1237AB Secretary may waive debts of a particular class</p>
</div>
</article>	<div id="view-last-reviewed-date">
		
		  
